      "amount": "3 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "Vegetable Oil",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "Cashews",
      "amount": "1/4 cup"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a wok over medium-high heat.",
    "Add papelon and cook until it browns slightly, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add garlic and green onions; sauté for an additional minute.",
    "Pour in soy sauce, mirin, broth, pepper flakes, and paprika powder. Stir to combine.",
    "Gradually add water while stirring continuously to prevent burning.",
    "Simmer until the mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in cashews and cook for another minute until heated through.",
    "Serve hot with steamed vegetables or sushi rice."
  ],
